+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Cfs3oMMyJfyjTjZMpASwC1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SPMaKbgUT2Q1JqYAjHe7BM","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-plugin-marketplace.md","content":"# Plugin Marketplace Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a plugin marketplace with registry, version resolver, sandboxed runner, review system, dependency graph, and a top-level `createMarketplace()` integration function.\n\n**Architecture:** Five independent modules under `src/` (registry, resolver, runner, reviews, deps), each exporting a factory function that returns the corresponding service interface. A top-level `src/index.ts` composes them via `createMarketplace()` which provides an `installPlugin()` workflow.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Node.js `vm` module, `semver` npm package, `better-sqlite3` for reviews persistence, `vitest` for testing.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Install dependencies and verify build toolchain\n\n**Step 1:** Run `npm install` to install all dependencies.\n**Step 2:** Run `npm run build` to verify TypeScript compiles (will fail because no source yet — that's fine, just confirming tooling works).\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Plugin Registry (`src/registry/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/registry/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/registry/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** In-memory `Map<string, Map<string, PluginManifest>>` keyed by name then version.\n\n```typescript\n// src/registry/index.ts\nimport type { PluginManifest, RegistryService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createRegistry(): RegistryService {\n  const plugins = new Map<string, Map<string, PluginManifest>>();\n\n  return {\n    register(manifest: PluginManifest): void {\n      if (!plugins.has(manifest.name)) {\n        plugins.set(manifest.name, new Map());\n      }\n      plugins.get(manifest.name)!.set(manifest.version, { ...manifest });\n    },\n\n    get(name: string): PluginManifest | null {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions || versions.size === 0) return null;\n      // Return latest version (last registered)\n      let latest: PluginManifest | null = null;\n      for (const m of versions.values()) {\n        latest = m;\n      }\n      return latest;\n    },\n\n    getVersion(name: string, version: string): PluginManifest | null {\n      return plugins.get(name)?.get(version) ?? null;\n    },\n\n    list(): PluginManifest[] {\n      const result: PluginManifest[] = [];\n      for (const versions of plugins.values()) {\n        for (const m of versions.values()) {\n          result.push(m);\n        }\n      }\n      return result;\n    },\n\n    search(query: string): PluginManifest[] {\n      const q = query.toLowerCase();\n      const result: PluginManifest[] = [];\n      for (const versions of plugins.values()) {\n        for (const m of versions.values()) {\n          if (\n            m.name.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||\n            m.description.toLowerCase().includes(q)\n          ) {\n            result.push(m);\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      return result;\n    },\n\n    remove(name: string, version: string): boolean {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions) return false;\n      const deleted = versions.delete(version);\n      if (versions.size === 0) plugins.delete(name);\n      return deleted;\n    },\n\n    listVersions(name: string): string[] {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions) return [];\n      return Array.from(versions.keys());\n    },\n\n    update(name: string, version: string, updates: Partial<PluginManifest>): void {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions) return;\n      const existing = versions.get(version);\n      if (!existing) return;\n      versions.set(version, { ...existing, ...updates, name, version });\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Version Resolver (`src/resolver/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/resolver/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/resolver/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** Thin wrapper around the `semver` package.\n\n```typescript\n// src/resolver/index.ts\nimport semver from 'semver';\nimport type { VersionConstraint, ResolvedVersion, ResolverService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createResolver(): ResolverService {\n  return {\n    resolve(constraints: VersionConstraint[], available: Record<string, string[]>): ResolvedVersion[] {\n      const results: ResolvedVersion[] = [];\n      for (const c of constraints) {\n        const versions = available[c.name];\n        if (!versions || versions.length === 0) continue;\n        const best = semver.maxSatisfying(versions, c.range);\n        if (best) {\n          results.push({ name: c.name, version: best, satisfies: c.range });\n        }\n      }\n      return results;\n    },\n\n    satisfies(version: string, range: string): boolean {\n      return semver.satisfies(version, range);\n    },\n\n    maxSatisfying(versions: string[], range: string): string | null {\n      return semver.maxSatisfying(versions, range);\n    },\n\n    validRange(range: string): boolean {\n      return semver.validRange(range) !== null;\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Sandboxed Runner (`src/runner/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/runner/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/runner/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** Uses Node.js `vm` module with `vm.Script` and `vm.createContext`.\n\n```typescript\n// src/runner/index.ts\nimport vm from 'node:vm';\nimport type { SandboxResult, RunnerService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createRunner(): RunnerService {\n  async function execute(code: string, context: Record<string, unknown> = {}): Promise<SandboxResult> {\n    return executeWithTimeout(code, 5000, context);\n  }\n\n  async function executeWithTimeout(\n    code: string,\n    timeoutMs: number,\n    context: Record<string, unknown> = {}\n  ): Promise<SandboxResult> {\n    const startMem = process.memoryUsage().heapUsed;\n    const start = performance.now();\n    try {\n      const sandbox = { ...context, __result: undefined as unknown };\n      const wrappedCode = `__result = (function() { ${code} })();`;\n      const ctx = vm.createContext(sandbox);\n      const script = new vm.Script(wrappedCode);\n      script.runInContext(ctx, { timeout: timeoutMs });\n      const duration = performance.now() - start;\n      const endMem = process.memoryUsage().heapUsed;\n      return {\n        success: true,\n        output: sandbox.__result,\n        duration,\n        memoryUsed: Math.max(0, endMem - startMem),\n      };\n    } catch (err: unknown) {\n      const duration = performance.now() - start;\n      const endMem = process.memoryUsage().heapUsed;\n      return {\n        success: false,\n        output: null,\n        duration,\n        memoryUsed: Math.max(0, endMem - startMem),\n        error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),\n      };\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { execute, executeWithTimeout };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Review System (`src/reviews/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/reviews/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/reviews/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** Uses `better-sqlite3` with an in-memory database for persistence.\n\n```typescript\n// src/reviews/index.ts\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport type { Review, ReviewService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createReviewService(): ReviewService {\n  const db = new Database(':memory:');\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.exec(`\n    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS reviews (\n      id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n      pluginName TEXT NOT NULL,\n      pluginVersion TEXT NOT NULL,\n      userId TEXT NOT NULL,\n      rating INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK(rating >= 1 AND rating <= 5),\n      comment TEXT NOT NULL,\n      flagged INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n      createdAt TEXT NOT NULL\n    )\n  `);\n\n  return {\n    addReview(review: Omit<Review, 'id' | 'createdAt' | 'flagged'>): Review {\n      const createdAt = new Date().toISOString();\n      const stmt = db.prepare(\n        `INSERT INTO reviews (pluginName, pluginVersion, userId, rating, comment, flagged, createdAt)\n         VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, 0, ?)`\n      );\n      const result = stmt.run(review.pluginName, review.pluginVersion, review.userId, review.rating, review.comment, createdAt);\n      return {\n        id: Number(result.lastInsertRowid),\n        pluginName: review.pluginName,\n        pluginVersion: review.pluginVersion,\n        userId: review.userId,\n        rating: review.rating,\n        comment: review.comment,\n        flagged: false,\n        createdAt,\n      };\n    },\n\n    getReviews(pluginName: string): Review[] {\n      const rows = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM reviews WHERE pluginName = ?').all(pluginName) as Array<Record<string, unknown>>;\n      return rows.map(mapRow);\n    },\n\n    getAverageRating(pluginName: string): number {\n      const row = db.prepare('SELECT AVG(rating) as avg FROM reviews WHERE pluginName = ? AND flagged = 0').get(pluginName) as { avg: number | null } | undefined;\n      return row?.avg ?? 0;\n    },\n\n    flagReview(reviewId: number): void {\n      db.prepare('UPDATE reviews SET flagged = 1 WHERE id = ?').run(reviewId);\n    },\n\n    getFlaggedReviews(): Review[] {\n      const rows = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM reviews WHERE flagged = 1').all() as Array<Record<string, unknown>>;\n      return rows.map(mapRow);\n    },\n\n    removeReview(reviewId: number): boolean {\n      const result = db.prepare('DELETE FROM reviews WHERE id = ?').run(reviewId);\n      return result.changes > 0;\n    },\n\n    getReviewsByUser(userId: string): Review[] {\n      const rows = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM reviews WHERE userId = ?').all(userId) as Array<Record<string, unknown>>;\n      return rows.map(mapRow);\n    },\n\n    getReviewCount(pluginName: string): number {\n      const row = db.prepare('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM reviews WHERE pluginName = ?').get(pluginName) as { count: number };\n      return row.count;\n    },\n  };\n}\n\nfunction mapRow(row: Record<string, unknown>): Review {\n  return {\n    id: row.id as number,\n    pluginName: row.pluginName as string,\n    pluginVersion: row.pluginVersion as string,\n    userId: row.userId as string,\n    rating: row.rating as number,\n    comment: row.comment as string,\n    flagged: (row.flagged as number) === 1,\n    createdAt: row.createdAt as string,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Dependency Graph (`src/deps/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/deps/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/deps/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** Graph traversal algorithms operating on the registry.\n\n```typescript\n// src/deps/index.ts\nimport type { DependencyNode, DepsService, RegistryService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createDepsService(): DepsService {\n  return {\n    buildTree(name: string, registry: RegistryService): DependencyNode {\n      const manifest = registry.get(name);\n      if (!manifest) return { name, version: 'unknown', dependencies: [] };\n      const children: DependencyNode[] = [];\n      for (const depName of Object.keys(manifest.dependencies)) {\n        children.push(this.buildTree(depName, registry));\n      }\n      return { name: manifest.name, version: manifest.version, dependencies: children };\n    },\n\n    detectCycles(name: string, registry: RegistryService): string[][] | null {\n      const cycles: string[][] = [];\n      const visited = new Set<string>();\n      const path: string[] = [];\n\n      const dfs = (current: string) => {\n        if (path.includes(current)) {\n          const cycleStart = path.indexOf(current);\n          cycles.push([...path.slice(cycleStart), current]);\n          return;\n        }\n        if (visited.has(current)) return;\n        path.push(current);\n        const manifest = registry.get(current);\n        if (manifest) {\n          for (const depName of Object.keys(manifest.dependencies)) {\n            dfs(depName);\n          }\n        }\n        path.pop();\n        visited.add(current);\n      };\n\n      dfs(name);\n      return cycles.length > 0 ? cycles : null;\n    },\n\n    topologicalSort(name: string, registry: RegistryService): string[] {\n      const result: string[] = [];\n      const visited = new Set<string>();\n      const visiting = new Set<string>();\n\n      const dfs = (current: string) => {\n        if (visited.has(current)) return;\n        if (visiting.has(current)) return; // cycle — skip\n        visiting.add(current);\n        const manifest = registry.get(current);\n        if (manifest) {\n          for (const depName of Object.keys(manifest.dependencies)) {\n            dfs(depName);\n          }\n        }\n        visiting.delete(current);\n        visited.add(current);\n        result.push(current);\n      };\n\n      dfs(name);\n      return result;\n    },\n\n    flattenDependencies(name: string, registry: RegistryService): string[] {\n      const deps = new Set<string>();\n      const visited = new Set<string>();\n\n      const collect = (current: string) => {\n        if (visited.has(current)) return;\n        visited.add(current);\n        const manifest = registry.get(current);\n        if (manifest) {\n          for (const depName of Object.keys(manifest.dependencies)) {\n            deps.add(depName);\n            collect(depName);\n          }\n        }\n      };\n\n      collect(name);\n      return Array.from(deps);\n    },\n\n    hasCircularDependency(name: string, registry: RegistryService): boolean {\n      return this.detectCycles(name, registry) !== null;\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Integration Layer (`src/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** Compose all services and provide `installPlugin()`.\n\n```typescript\n// src/index.ts\nimport { createRegistry } from './registry/index.js';\nimport { createResolver } from './resolver/index.js';\nimport { createRunner } from './runner/index.js';\nimport { createReviewService } from './reviews/index.js';\nimport { createDepsService } from './deps/index.js';\nimport type {\n  PluginManifest,\n  RegistryService,\n  ResolverService,\n  RunnerService,\n  ReviewService,\n  DepsService,\n  ResolvedVersion,\n  SandboxResult,\n} from './types.js';\n\nexport interface Marketplace {\n  registry: RegistryService;\n  resolver: ResolverService;\n  runner: RunnerService;\n  reviews: ReviewService;\n  deps: DepsService;\n  installPlugin(manifest: PluginManifest): Promise<{\n    resolved: ResolvedVersion[];\n    result: SandboxResult;\n  }>;\n}\n\nexport function createMarketplace(): Marketplace {\n  const registry = createRegistry();\n  const resolver = createResolver();\n  const runner = createRunner();\n  const reviews = createReviewService();\n  const deps = createDepsService();\n\n  return {\n    registry,\n    resolver,\n    runner,\n    reviews,\n    deps,\n    async installPlugin(manifest: PluginManifest) {\n      // Validate required fields\n      if (!manifest.name || !manifest.version || !manifest.entryPoint) {\n        throw new Error('Plugin manifest must have name, version, and entryPoint');\n      }\n\n      // Register the plugin\n      registry.register(manifest);\n\n      // Resolve dependency versions\n      const constraints = Object.entries(manifest.dependencies).map(\n        ([name, range]) => ({ name, range })\n      );\n      const available: Record<string, string[]> = {};\n      for (const name of Object.keys(manifest.dependencies)) {\n        available[name] = registry.listVersions(name);\n      }\n      const resolved = resolver.resolve(constraints, available);\n\n      // Check for circular dependencies\n      if (deps.hasCircularDependency(manifest.name, registry)) {\n        throw new Error('Circular dependency detected');\n      }\n\n      // Execute the plugin entry point\n      const result = await runner.execute(manifest.entryPoint);\n\n      return { resolved, result };\n    },\n  };\n}\n\nexport { createRegistry } from './registry/index.js';\nexport { createResolver } from './resolver/index.js';\nexport { createRunner } from './runner/index.js';\nexport { createReviewService } from './reviews/index.js';\nexport { createDepsService } from './deps/index.js';\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Write tests for all modules\n\nCreate test files for each module covering key behaviors.\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Build, lint, test\n\nRun `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, `npm test` and fix any issues.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":119,"cache_read_input_tokens":22064,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":119},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1483fefa-e217-49f3-8e12-5354d1be214b","uuid":"1ec51c0f-6d48-4200-854b-57cf9e98e1d7"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SPMaKbgUT2Q1JqYAjHe7BM","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-plugin-marketplace.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1483fefa-e217-49f3-8e12-5354d1be214b","uuid":"45b88f46-d264-4eb5-a4ed-7a60e6f3c415","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-plugin-marketplace.md","content":"# Plugin Marketplace Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a plugin marketplace with registry, version resolver, sandboxed runner, review system, dependency graph, and a top-level `createMarketplace()` integration function.\n\n**Architecture:** Five independent modules under `src/` (registry, resolver, runner, reviews, deps), each exporting a factory function that returns the corresponding service interface. A top-level `src/index.ts` composes them via `createMarketplace()` which provides an `installPlugin()` workflow.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Node.js `vm` module, `semver` npm package, `better-sqlite3` for reviews persistence, `vitest` for testing.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Install dependencies and verify build toolchain\n\n**Step 1:** Run `npm install` to install all dependencies.\n**Step 2:** Run `npm run build` to verify TypeScript compiles (will fail because no source yet — that's fine, just confirming tooling works).\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Plugin Registry (`src/registry/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/registry/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/registry/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** In-memory `Map<string, Map<string, PluginManifest>>` keyed by name then version.\n\n```typescript\n// src/registry/index.ts\nimport type { PluginManifest, RegistryService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createRegistry(): RegistryService {\n  const plugins = new Map<string, Map<string, PluginManifest>>();\n\n  return {\n    register(manifest: PluginManifest): void {\n      if (!plugins.has(manifest.name)) {\n        plugins.set(manifest.name, new Map());\n      }\n      plugins.get(manifest.name)!.set(manifest.version, { ...manifest });\n    },\n\n    get(name: string): PluginManifest | null {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions || versions.size === 0) return null;\n      // Return latest version (last registered)\n      let latest: PluginManifest | null = null;\n      for (const m of versions.values()) {\n        latest = m;\n      }\n      return latest;\n    },\n\n    getVersion(name: string, version: string): PluginManifest | null {\n      return plugins.get(name)?.get(version) ?? null;\n    },\n\n    list(): PluginManifest[] {\n      const result: PluginManifest[] = [];\n      for (const versions of plugins.values()) {\n        for (const m of versions.values()) {\n          result.push(m);\n        }\n      }\n      return result;\n    },\n\n    search(query: string): PluginManifest[] {\n      const q = query.toLowerCase();\n      const result: PluginManifest[] = [];\n      for (const versions of plugins.values()) {\n        for (const m of versions.values()) {\n          if (\n            m.name.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||\n            m.description.toLowerCase().includes(q)\n          ) {\n            result.push(m);\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      return result;\n    },\n\n    remove(name: string, version: string): boolean {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions) return false;\n      const deleted = versions.delete(version);\n      if (versions.size === 0) plugins.delete(name);\n      return deleted;\n    },\n\n    listVersions(name: string): string[] {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions) return [];\n      return Array.from(versions.keys());\n    },\n\n    update(name: string, version: string, updates: Partial<PluginManifest>): void {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions) return;\n      const existing = versions.get(version);\n      if (!existing) return;\n      versions.set(version, { ...existing, ...updates, name, version });\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Version Resolver (`src/resolver/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/resolver/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/resolver/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** Thin wrapper around the `semver` package.\n\n```typescript\n// src/resolver/index.ts\nimport semver from 'semver';\nimport type { VersionConstraint, ResolvedVersion, ResolverService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createResolver(): ResolverService {\n  return {\n    resolve(constraints: VersionConstraint[], available: Record<string, string[]>): ResolvedVersion[] {\n      const results: ResolvedVersion[] = [];\n      for (const c of constraints) {\n        const versions = available[c.name];\n        if (!versions || versions.length === 0) continue;\n        const best = semver.maxSatisfying(versions, c.range);\n        if (best) {\n          results.push({ name: c.name, version: best, satisfies: c.range });\n        }\n      }\n      return results;\n    },\n\n    satisfies(version: string, range: string): boolean {\n      return semver.satisfies(version, range);\n    },\n\n    maxSatisfying(versions: string[], range: string): string | null {\n      return semver.maxSatisfying(versions, range);\n    },\n\n    validRange(range: string): boolean {\n      return semver.validRange(range) !== null;\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Sandboxed Runner (`src/runner/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/runner/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/runner/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** Uses Node.js `vm` module with `vm.Script` and `vm.createContext`.\n\n```typescript\n// src/runner/index.ts\nimport vm from 'node:vm';\nimport type { SandboxResult, RunnerService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createRunner(): RunnerService {\n  async function execute(code: string, context: Record<string, unknown> = {}): Promise<SandboxResult> {\n    return executeWithTimeout(code, 5000, context);\n  }\n\n  async function executeWithTimeout(\n    code: string,\n    timeoutMs: number,\n    context: Record<string, unknown> = {}\n  ): Promise<SandboxResult> {\n    const startMem = process.memoryUsage().heapUsed;\n    const start = performance.now();\n    try {\n      const sandbox = { ...context, __result: undefined as unknown };\n      const wrappedCode = `__result = (function() { ${code} })();`;\n      const ctx = vm.createContext(sandbox);\n      const script = new vm.Script(wrappedCode);\n      script.runInContext(ctx, { timeout: timeoutMs });\n      const duration = performance.now() - start;\n      const endMem = process.memoryUsage().heapUsed;\n      return {\n        success: true,\n        output: sandbox.__result,\n        duration,\n        memoryUsed: Math.max(0, endMem - startMem),\n      };\n    } catch (err: unknown) {\n      const duration = performance.now() - start;\n      const endMem = process.memoryUsage().heapUsed;\n      return {\n        success: false,\n        output: null,\n        duration,\n        memoryUsed: Math.max(0, endMem - startMem),\n        error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),\n      };\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { execute, executeWithTimeout };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Review System (`src/reviews/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/reviews/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/reviews/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** Uses `better-sqlite3` with an in-memory database for persistence.\n\n```typescript\n// src/reviews/index.ts\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport type { Review, ReviewService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createReviewService(): ReviewService {\n  const db = new Database(':memory:');\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.exec(`\n    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS reviews (\n      id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n      pluginName TEXT NOT NULL,\n      pluginVersion TEXT NOT NULL,\n      userId TEXT NOT NULL,\n      rating INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK(rating >= 1 AND rating <= 5),\n      comment TEXT NOT NULL,\n      flagged INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n      createdAt TEXT NOT NULL\n    )\n  `);\n\n  return {\n    addReview(review: Omit<Review, 'id' | 'createdAt' | 'flagged'>): Review {\n      const createdAt = new Date().toISOString();\n      const stmt = db.prepare(\n        `INSERT INTO reviews (pluginName, pluginVersion, userId, rating, comment, flagged, createdAt)\n         VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, 0, ?)`\n      );\n      const result = stmt.run(review.pluginName, review.pluginVersion, review.userId, review.rating, review.comment, createdAt);\n      return {\n        id: Number(result.lastInsertRowid),\n        pluginName: review.pluginName,\n        pluginVersion: review.pluginVersion,\n        userId: review.userId,\n        rating: review.rating,\n        comment: review.comment,\n        flagged: false,\n        createdAt,\n      };\n    },\n\n    getReviews(pluginName: string): Review[] {\n      const rows = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM reviews WHERE pluginName = ?').all(pluginName) as Array<Record<string, unknown>>;\n      return rows.map(mapRow);\n    },\n\n    getAverageRating(pluginName: string): number {\n      const row = db.prepare('SELECT AVG(rating) as avg FROM reviews WHERE pluginName = ? AND flagged = 0').get(pluginName) as { avg: number | null } | undefined;\n      return row?.avg ?? 0;\n    },\n\n    flagReview(reviewId: number): void {\n      db.prepare('UPDATE reviews SET flagged = 1 WHERE id = ?').run(reviewId);\n    },\n\n    getFlaggedReviews(): Review[] {\n      const rows = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM reviews WHERE flagged = 1').all() as Array<Record<string, unknown>>;\n      return rows.map(mapRow);\n    },\n\n    removeReview(reviewId: number): boolean {\n      const result = db.prepare('DELETE FROM reviews WHERE id = ?').run(reviewId);\n      return result.changes > 0;\n    },\n\n    getReviewsByUser(userId: string): Review[] {\n      const rows = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM reviews WHERE userId = ?').all(userId) as Array<Record<string, unknown>>;\n      return rows.map(mapRow);\n    },\n\n    getReviewCount(pluginName: string): number {\n      const row = db.prepare('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM reviews WHERE pluginName = ?').get(pluginName) as { count: number };\n      return row.count;\n    },\n  };\n}\n\nfunction mapRow(row: Record<string, unknown>): Review {\n  return {\n    id: row.id as number,\n    pluginName: row.pluginName as string,\n    pluginVersion: row.pluginVersion as string,\n    userId: row.userId as string,\n    rating: row.rating as number,\n    comment: row.comment as string,\n    flagged: (row.flagged as number) === 1,\n    createdAt: row.createdAt as string,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Dependency Graph (`src/deps/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/deps/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/deps/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** Graph traversal algorithms operating on the registry.\n\n```typescript\n// src/deps/index.ts\nimport type { DependencyNode, DepsService, RegistryService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createDepsService(): DepsService {\n  return {\n    buildTree(name: string, registry: RegistryService): DependencyNode {\n      const manifest = registry.get(name);\n      if (!manifest) return { name, version: 'unknown', dependencies: [] };\n      const children: DependencyNode[] = [];\n      for (const depName of Object.keys(manifest.dependencies)) {\n        children.push(this.buildTree(depName, registry));\n      }\n      return { name: manifest.name, version: manifest.version, dependencies: children };\n    },\n\n    detectCycles(name: string, registry: RegistryService): string[][] | null {\n      const cycles: string[][] = [];\n      const visited = new Set<string>();\n      const path: string[] = [];\n\n      const dfs = (current: string) => {\n        if (path.includes(current)) {\n          const cycleStart = path.indexOf(current);\n          cycles.push([...path.slice(cycleStart), current]);\n          return;\n        }\n        if (visited.has(current)) return;\n        path.push(current);\n        const manifest = registry.get(current);\n        if (manifest) {\n          for (const depName of Object.keys(manifest.dependencies)) {\n            dfs(depName);\n          }\n        }\n        path.pop();\n        visited.add(current);\n      };\n\n      dfs(name);\n      return cycles.length > 0 ? cycles : null;\n    },\n\n    topologicalSort(name: string, registry: RegistryService): string[] {\n      const result: string[] = [];\n      const visited = new Set<string>();\n      const visiting = new Set<string>();\n\n      const dfs = (current: string) => {\n        if (visited.has(current)) return;\n        if (visiting.has(current)) return; // cycle — skip\n        visiting.add(current);\n        const manifest = registry.get(current);\n        if (manifest) {\n          for (const depName of Object.keys(manifest.dependencies)) {\n            dfs(depName);\n          }\n        }\n        visiting.delete(current);\n        visited.add(current);\n        result.push(current);\n      };\n\n      dfs(name);\n      return result;\n    },\n\n    flattenDependencies(name: string, registry: RegistryService): string[] {\n      const deps = new Set<string>();\n      const visited = new Set<string>();\n\n      const collect = (current: string) => {\n        if (visited.has(current)) return;\n        visited.add(current);\n        const manifest = registry.get(current);\n        if (manifest) {\n          for (const depName of Object.keys(manifest.dependencies)) {\n            deps.add(depName);\n            collect(depName);\n          }\n        }\n      };\n\n      collect(name);\n      return Array.from(deps);\n    },\n\n    hasCircularDependency(name: string, registry: RegistryService): boolean {\n      return this.detectCycles(name, registry) !== null;\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Integration Layer (`src/index.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n- Test: `src/index.test.ts`\n\n**Implementation:** Compose all services and provide `installPlugin()`.\n\n```typescript\n// src/index.ts\nimport { createRegistry } from './registry/index.js';\nimport { createResolver } from './resolver/index.js';\nimport { createRunner } from './runner/index.js';\nimport { createReviewService } from './reviews/index.js';\nimport { createDepsService } from './deps/index.js';\nimport type {\n  PluginManifest,\n  RegistryService,\n  ResolverService,\n  RunnerService,\n  ReviewService,\n  DepsService,\n  ResolvedVersion,\n  SandboxResult,\n} from './types.js';\n\nexport interface Marketplace {\n  registry: RegistryService;\n  resolver: ResolverService;\n  runner: RunnerService;\n  reviews: ReviewService;\n  deps: DepsService;\n  installPlugin(manifest: PluginManifest): Promise<{\n    resolved: ResolvedVersion[];\n    result: SandboxResult;\n  }>;\n}\n\nexport function createMarketplace(): Marketplace {\n  const registry = createRegistry();\n  const resolver = createResolver();\n  const runner = createRunner();\n  const reviews = createReviewService();\n  const deps = createDepsService();\n\n  return {\n    registry,\n    resolver,\n    runner,\n    reviews,\n    deps,\n    async installPlugin(manifest: PluginManifest) {\n      // Validate required fields\n      if (!manifest.name || !manifest.version || !manifest.entryPoint) {\n        throw new Error('Plugin manifest must have name, version, and entryPoint');\n      }\n\n      // Register the plugin\n      registry.register(manifest);\n\n      // Resolve dependency versions\n      const constraints = Object.entries(manifest.dependencies).map(\n        ([name, range]) => ({ name, range })\n      );\n      const available: Record<string, string[]> = {};\n      for (const name of Object.keys(manifest.dependencies)) {\n        available[name] = registry.listVersions(name);\n      }\n      const resolved = resolver.resolve(constraints, available);\n\n      // Check for circular dependencies\n      if (deps.hasCircularDependency(manifest.name, registry)) {\n        throw new Error('Circular dependency detected');\n      }\n\n      // Execute the plugin entry point\n      const result = await runner.execute(manifest.entryPoint);\n\n      return { resolved, result };\n    },\n  };\n}\n\nexport { createRegistry } from './registry/index.js';\nexport { createResolver } from './resolver/index.js';\nexport { createRunner } from './runner/index.js';\nexport { createReviewService } from './reviews/index.js';\nexport { createDepsService } from './deps/index.js';\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Write tests for all modules\n\nCreate test files for each module covering key behaviors.\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Build, lint, test\n\nRun `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, `npm test` and fix any issues.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
